  "texts": [
    "Here, AI was more original thus indicating higher creative potential, but this metric may more appropriately reflect the advancement of the algorithms these models were trained on in conjunction with human input.",
    "In other words, AI, unlike humans, does not have agency, thus AI creative potentials are dependent on the assistance of a human user to elicit responses.",
    "Therefore, the creative potential of AI is in a constant state of stagnation unless prompted.",
    "Moreover, researchers have examined the interplay between creative potential and real-world creative achievements 54, 55 but this approach assumes human level creativity and is not able to account for artificial intelligence.",
    "AI can generate creative ideas, but it cannot be assumed that this potential would translate to achievement."
  ],
